{"title_page": "Michael Weston", "text_new": "{{about|the actor|the character from ''Burn Notice''|Michael Westen}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image       = Michael Weston by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| imagesize   = 220px\n| caption     = Weston in 2016\n| birth_name  = Michael Rubinstein<ref>{{cite web|title=Michael Weston|url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/michael-weston/166362/|website=[[TV Guide]]}}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1973|10|25}}\n| birth_place = [[New York City|New York, New York]], U.S.\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| yearsactive = 1998&ndash;present\n| spouse      = [[Priscilla Ahn]] (2010&ndash;present)\n| parents     = [[John Rubinstein]]<br />[[Judi West]]\n| occupation  = Actor\n}}\n'''Michael Weston''' (born '''Michael Rubinstein'''; October 25, 1973) is an American television and film actor. His best-known roles are the private detective [[Lucas Douglas]] on ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'', the deranged and sadistic kidnapper Jake in the [[HBO]] drama ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'' and Pvt. Dancer on ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nMichael Rubinstein was born in [[New York City]], the son of actors [[John Rubinstein]] and [[Judi West]]. His paternal grandfather is Polish-born [[Jewish]] piano virtuoso [[Arthur Rubinstein]]. He is also the great-grandson of Polish conductor [[Emil M\u0142ynarski]], the founding conductor of the [[Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra]] and principal conductor of the [[Scottish Orchestra]].<ref>[http://www.filmreference.com/film/10/Michael-Weston.html Michael Weston profile], filmreference.com; accessed October 8, 2014.</ref>\n\nHe holds a degree in Theater and Arts from [[Northwestern University]]. In 2000 he changed his surname to \"Weston\" as there was already a \"Michael Rubinstein\" in the [[Screen Actors Guild]].\n\n==Acting career==\nWeston is a good friend of actor [[Zach Braff]] and has appeared in three features with him, ''[[Garden State (film)|Garden State]],'' ''[[Wish I Was Here]]'' and ''[[The Last Kiss (2006 film)|The Last Kiss]]'', and as a guest star on Braff's television show, ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]''. Weston has also appeared as Simon Marsden, [[Olivia Benson|Olivia Benson's]] half-brother on ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''.<ref name=\"imdb\"/>\n\nWeston appeared in the fifth season of ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' as a private investigator named Lucas Douglas hired by Dr. Gregory House; he reappeared in season six.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Weston On House-Cuddy-Lucas Love Triangle: \"It's an Intellectual Menage a Trois\"|url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/michael-weston-house-1013570/|accessdate=October 15, 2016|work=TVGuide.com|date=January 11, 2010}}</ref> Series creator [[David Shore]] planned a spin-off show<ref name=\"House\">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/a120107/house-creator-reveals-spinoff-plans.html|title=''House'' creator reveals spinoff plans|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|date=2008-08-07|work=Digital Spy|publisher=Digital Spy|accessdate=2008-09-04}}</ref> with Weston's character as the lead in 2008, but the show never went into production.\n\nIn 2009, Weston appeared in the [[Gerard Butler]] action film ''[[Gamer (2009 film)|Gamer]]''. He made a guest appearance on ''[[White Collar (TV series)|White Collar]]''<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Weston for 'White Collar' role|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ustv/news/a377199/house-actor-michael-weston-for-white-collar-role/|accessdate=October 15, 2016|work=Digital Spy|date=April 18, 2012}}</ref> and ''[[Burn Notice]]'' (in which the main character, [[Michael Westen]], has a name very similar to his). In 2012, he starred in the [[A&E Networks|A&E]] television movie, ''[[Coma (US miniseries)|Coma]]''.<ref name=\"imdb\">{{IMDb name|922995}}{{unreliable source?|date=March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, he appeared as [[Harry Houdini]] in ''[[Houdini & Doyle]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Power|first1=Vicki|title=Michael Weston and Stephen Mangan stars in new ITV crime drama Houdini & Doyle|url=http://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/650472/Michael-Weston-Stephen-Mangan-star-ITV-crime-drama-Houdini-and-Doyle|accessdate= October 15, 2016|work=The Express|date=March 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nRubinstein has been married to musician [[Priscilla Ahn]] since 2010.<ref name=\"imdb\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Year\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Role\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 2000 || ''[[Coyote Ugly (film)|Coyote Ugly]]'' || Danny ||\n|-\n| ''[[Sally (2000 film)|Sally]]'' || Bugs || Credited as Michael Rubinstein\n|-\n| ''[[Lucky Numbers]]'' || Larry || \n|- \n| ''[[Cherry Falls]]'' || Ben ||\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2002 || ''[[Wishcraft]]'' || Brett Bumpers ||\n|-\n| ''[[Hart's War]]'' || Pfc. W. Roy Potts ||\n|-\n| ''[[Evil Alien Conquerors]]'' || Kenny ||\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2004 || ''[[Helter Skelter (2004 film)|Helter Skelter]]'' || [[Bobby Beausoleil]] || [[Television movie]]\n|-\n| ''[[Garden State (film)|Garden State]]'' || Kenny ||\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[The Dukes of Hazzard (film)|The Dukes of Hazzard]]'' || Deputy Enos Strate || \n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[The Last Kiss (2006 film)|The Last Kiss]]'' || Izzy || \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Wedding Daze]]'' || Ted ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Pathology (film)|Pathology]]'' || Dr. Gallo ||\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2009 || ''[[State of Play (film)|State of Play]]'' || Hank ||\n|-\n| ''[[Crank: High Voltage]]'' || Paramedic ||\n|-\n| ''[[Gamer (2009 film)|Gamer]]'' || The producer ||\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Love, Wedding, Marriage]]'' || Gerber ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[The Brooklyn Brothers Beat the Best]]'' || Jim ||\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Liberal Arts (film)|Liberal Arts]]'' || Miles ||\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Expecting (film)|Expecting]]'' || Casey ||\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Wish I Was Here]]'' || Jerry ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[See You in Valhalla]]'' || Don Burwood || \n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Gravy (film)|Gravy]]'' || Anson || \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Year\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Role\n! style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Notes\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[Night Man]]'' || || Episode: 1.17 \"Chrome II\"\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Frasier]]'' || Ice Sculptor || Episode: 10.14 \"Daphne Does Dinner\"\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Monk (TV series)|Monk]]'' || Morris || Episode: 3.7 \"[[Mr. Monk and the Employee of the Month]]\"\n|-\n| 2004\u20132005 || ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'' || Jake || Episodes: <br> 4.5 [[List of Six Feet Under episodes#Season 4 (2004)|\"That's My Dog\"]] <br> 4.8 \"Coming And Going\" <br> 4.12 \"Untitled\" <br> 5.10 \"All Alone\" \n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'' || Rafe Hendricks || Episodes: <br> 12.22 \"[[Twenty-One Guns (ER)|Twenty-One Guns]]\" <br> 13.1 \"[[Bloodline (ER)|Bloodline]]\"\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Saved (TV series)|Saved]]'' || Tim Reston || Episode: 1.2 \"The Lady & the Tiger\"\n|-\n| 2007, 2014 || ''[[Psych]]'' || Counselor Adam Hornstock || Episode: <br> 1.12 \"[[Cloudy...Chance of Murder]]\" <br> 8.3 \"[[Psych (season 8)#ep113|Remake A.K.A. Cloudy... With a Chance of Improvement]]\"\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]'' || [[Private (rank)|Private]] Brian Dancer || Episodes: <br> 6.7 \"[[His Story IV]]\" <br> 6.9 \"[[My Perspective]]\" <br> 6.10 \"[[My Therapeutic Month]]\" <br> 6.12 \"[[My Fishbowl]]\" \n|-\n| 2007, 2012, 2019 || ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'' || Simon Marsden || Episodes: <br> 8.13 \"Loophole\" <br> 8.16 \"Philadelphia\" <br> 8.19 \"Florida\" <br> 8.22 \"Screwed\" <br> 13.16 \"Child\u2019s Welfare\" <br> 21.6 \"Murdered at a Bad Address\"\n|-\n| 2008\u20132010 || ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' || Lucas Douglas || Episodes: <br> 5.2 \"[[Not Cancer (House)|Not Cancer]]\" <br> 5.3 \"Adverse Events\" <br> 5.5 \"Lucky Thirteen\" 